/*
 * Improved single-file webcrawler in C
 * - No libcurl
 * - Supports HTTP and HTTPS (OpenSSL)
 * - Uses POSIX sockets, OpenSSL, libxml2
 * - Handles redirects, chunked transfer decoding, basic gzip passthrough (no decompression)
 * - Extracts links and visible assets (href/src, link rel=stylesheet, script, img, audio, video, source)
 * - Parses CSS url(...) patterns for assets
 * - Respects robots.txt (basic disallow parsing)
 * - Politeness: per-host rate limiting and concurrent worker threads
 * - Persistent in-memory URL set implemented as a chained hash table with crawled flag
 * - Saves files under output/<host>/<path> preserving directory structure
 *
 * Build:
 *   gcc -O2 -pthread -o crawler crawler.c -lxml2 -lssl -lcrypto
 *
 * Usage:
 *   ./crawler <start-url> [max-threads]
 *
 * Notes and limitations:
 * - This is an educational example, not production-grade.
 * - TLS certificate verification is minimal (hostname check is not fully robust).
 * - No HTTP/2 support.
 * - No automatic gzip/deflate decompression (content saved as received).
 * - robots.txt parsing is simplistic and may not cover all rules.
 * - Error handling is improved but still simplified.
 */

